inn1.comm: starts the big game with a bouncer. Wide called. Too high above the head.
slightly short of length, outside the off stump, pushed to point
bit of bounce, from back of length, Sehwag gets an inside edge as he tries to force it off the back foot

There he goes. Throws his bat at a short of length delivery outside off and it flies straight where the third slip would stand and down to the thirdman. Short and wide, and he can't resist freeing his arms.
on the body, tickled around the corner
right on the money, on the off stump line, on a length, pushed away to the off side
Sehwag tries to drill a length delivery down the ground but is beaten a touch by the late in swing. Gets an inside edge which takes the ball to mid-on
beaten outside off stump. Bradshaw takes this one away with the angle and Sehwag tries to force it but can't connect&
Sehwag was much more conservative this time. Leant fully to a length delivery outside off and pushed it to cover
Bradshaw continues to hit the right areas. Again another drew Sehwag forward and whizzed past his outside edge
And this time the inner edge. Sehwag went for a on-the-up drive through the off side ended up going outside the line and gets a single as the ball runs to shortish fine-leg
Angled across Tendulkar, well outside the off stump and left alone
The new wood works perfectly. Carved past point. High back-lift, and a ferocious tap on the head of the ball.
on the hips, whipped to fine-leg
Tendulkar remains on 0. Leans forward to a length delivery on the off stump line and pushes it to cover

And West Indies continue to ping outside- the- off-stump line at Tendulkar. Australia have done it in the past, making Tendulkar reach for deliveries. This time Tendulkar lets it go through to the 'keeper
fuller and outside the off stump, Tendulkar leans forward to defend it away
Runako Morton gets his body behind to save another cracking drive from Sehwag. Just a single. Overpitched outside the off stump, Sehwag frees his arms and mind
kicks up slightly from back of length, outside the off stump, Tendulkar gets across, reaches out to dab it to thirdman region
on the middle and off, length delivery and Sehwag respects both the line and length

Dwayne Smith, at point, misses a easy chance to run out Sehwag. Sehwag pushed it to left of Smith, set off for a run but Tendulkar sent him back but by that time it looked too late. Smith moved to his left, made the stop and had a shy, Sehwag had given up attempting to get back but Smith missed the stumps
slipping down the leg side
on the middle and leg, a length delivery, Tendulkar punches it away through midwicket.
Full and outside the off stump, Sehwag drives  but straight to cover
Sehwag jumps at a short delivery outside the off stump to cut it past backward point. Down comes the bat from its apogee in a hurry to belt the ball past point.

Taylor, the hero against Australia, gets Sehwag. Traps him in front. Sehwag is caught way back at his crease and length delivery veered in and crashed into his pads. Hit in front of middle and leg. The bat came down in an angle and couldnt make contact with the ball that had nipped back after landing.
just on the off stump line, defended off the front foot
Ouch. Taylor pings Pathan with a snorter. Rears up straight at the body and Pathan takes his eyes off and tries to duck under but ......
orgasmic straight drive from Tendulkar. It was full and down came the blade, beautifully straight, sending the ball screaming past the stumps at the other end
He tries to drill past point this time but finds the man. Fullish outside the off stump and Tendulkar goes for a square-drive
length delivery on the off stump line, punched to cover
Length delivery on the middle and off, Pathan's bat  comes down slightly outside the line and gets an inside edge to the on side

And another inside edge and this time it is fatal. Pathan goes for a drive on-the-up   to a length delivery slanting outside the off stump and drags it back to his stumps. West Indies are on a roll here.
leans forward to a length delivery on the off stump, pushes it to cover. No chance of a run. West Indies are applying the chokehold here.
Noose tightens further. Taylor sucks Tendulkar into a near-fatal drive outside the offstump. Beaten.
Tendulkar resists greed, goes middleclass on this one. Leans forward to defend.
And turns into a monk now. Shoulders arms to a delivery outside off

Ah... Taylor pings the right shoulder of Tendulkar with a snorter. Climbs up at a rapid pace and Tendulkar actually did well to sway away from it with just a hit to his body. Managed to get his bat away from the line.
Will Tendulkar attempt to hit back? Taylor tries by offering one on a length outside off, Tendulkar answers with non-violence. Patted back gently.
Bradshaw, meanwhile, continues to tempt Tendulkar with fullish deliveries well outside the offstump. Resisted again by the little big man.
strays on the pads, flicked away to long-leg.
on the middle and Dravid really stretches his left foot well forward to defend
And another one well outside the off stump, left alone
on the middle and leg, whipped to Bravo at square-leg. Another tight over comes to an end.
Hmm.. Tendulkar gets off strike with a dab to thirdman region. Short of length and outside off, pushed away.

Almost had him lbw as well. But going down. Neither Taylor nor anybody behind the wicket appealed. I can think of more than a few cricketers who would have yelled like idiots for it. It was full and Dravid fell over a bit while trying to work it to the on side
Nearly dragged it back to the stumps. Short and wide outside the off stump, Dravid goes for a horizontal shot but the ball keeps a touch low and the ball runs to left of Baugh
on the middle and leg and bit of bounce there. Dravid hopped back and tried to work it behind square-leg but ended up pushing straight to Smith there.
Smith at square point comes into play as Tendulkar square-drives a fullish ball outside off stump to him.

Two close men on the off and the ball is whipped through the midwicket gap. Full and on the off and middle, Tendulkar brings his wrists into play. Bravo makes a valiant effort near the ropes, umpire refers it upstairs and a four is declared after replays.
Now the short-cover comes into play. Chris Gayle is the man there. Tendulkar tries to go on the up but doesn't time it well
leans fully forward to push a fullish delivery to cover point
Again mistimes. Has happened a few times whenever he has tried to force it through the line. Bradshaw makes the stop.
hit on the pads but again West Indies don't appeal unnecessarily. It was going down leg. Full and bit of curve in.
slipping down the leg side.
Well outside the off stump, left alone
Not on the legs son. whipped through the midwicket gap
Left alone or did he play it?! It was a length delivery outside the off stump and Dravid looked to do both but finally managed to pull his bat out of line
Dravid pulls but straight to Dwayne Smith at square-leg. Short of length delivery on the middle and Dravid rocks back to pull.  A shot that was seen quite a lot early in his career.
And this time the cut. But again the placement is not great. Straight to point
length delivery on the off, pushed to cover

Smith almost gets Tendulkar! With the one that comes back in a touch after landing on a length around the middle. This delivery has troubled Tendulkar in the past, and could have had him this time if umpire Harper was more generous. To the bowler ie. Hit him high on the pads, Hawk-Eye suggests it would have taken the bail of the middle out.
Creamed through the covers. Overpitched outside off and Tendulkar muscles it away
Dravid pings the cover fence. Delectable drive. Head over the ball, feet upto the pitch and al that jazz. Overpitched loosener from Bravo.
Nearly finds the lond-leg boundary. On the legs, full in length, Why o why you would bowl to him there, whipped away
tip and run. Pushed to right of point and away they run
too eary into his drive and the ball rolls towards mid-off.
Leans forward well this time to square-drive a fullish ball past point.
Just outside the offstump, gentle seam-up stuff, Dravid taps it to the off side
Almost a lbw. That left foot of Dravid stretches out too much across and he ends up playing around it but manages to make contact.
No pace to work with. Length delivery, just outside the off stump, punched away to cover.
outside the off and dabbed to thirdman
On the middle and off but Tendulkar wrists it away to long-leg.
Pulled through the midwicket gap. Slightly short and Dravid presses back, both feet in the air, and places it in the gap
full and on the legs, should have put it away for a boundary. Instead finds the man at long-leg
legcutter on the off, pushed to cover point
Gayle goes down in a hurry at short cover to make a very good stop. Tendulkar had punched a slightly short-of-length delivery to his left.
short-arm-jab cum punch but can't beat cover point. Hit on the up but straight to the fielder
will retain the strike as he gets a outside edge to thirdman while trying to force a length delivery through the off side ring.
Driven smoothly but straight to point
Finds the gap this time. Full and outside off, Tendulkar drills it past extra cover
on the hips, whipped behind square-leg

beaten as he tries to steer a delivery outside the off stump to thirdman. Interestingly, Lara at slip had moved to his right even as he saw Dravid attempting to steer. Could have been interesting had Dravid made contact
overpitched outside off, driven powerfully but straight to mid-off
Slipping down the leg side. smart work by Baugh. Whips off the bails in a flash but Dravid is inside his crease.
Tendulkar paddles a length delivery from Bradshaw, out to long-leg. Predetermined, of course.
on the middle and leg, ticked around the corner
on the stumps, turned to midwicket

And Tendulkar is gone! Drags a widish ball back to his stumps. Bradshaw pushes one full and well outside the off stump - much more wider than what he had been doing early in the day - and Tendulkar chases after it, goes for a drive but ends up plotting his own demise.
Yuvraj Singh is beaten neck and crop. Bradshaw makes that one land on a length, drawing Yuvraj forward, before taking it away, much to the chagrin of the batsman
fullish, just outside the off, Dravid drives but too much bottom-hand and the ball rolls to mid-off
on the middle and leg, tucked to Samuels in front of square-leg

Dravid tries to tip and run but ends up tipping it too much and hence can't run. Well what happened was that he pushed a length delivery outside off a bit too hard than he had intended and Smith rushed across towards the ball, killing any thought of a run.
pushed to mid-on. Not even a thought of a run this time.
On the middle, Dravid gets into a tangle trying to work it to the onside. Ends up turning it straight to midwicket
in the zone outside off, left alone
Angles it in in an attempt to trap him in front but ends up pushing it bit too much. Although it rapped Yuvraj, who fell over a bit, in the pads but it was going down the leg side
just outside the off stump, Yuvraj pushes at it with a opened-face of the bat and steers it to point
Overpitched, driven to cover
length delivery on the middle, tucked to right of midwicket
overpitched outside off, driven to cover
Again no pace to work with. Slanted delivery outside off, carved to point
Dravid tries to break free with a forcing-drive off the back foot but can't pierce the cover ring
Yuvraj gets away with a sliced-four over point. Short and wide, and he frees his arms
Bravo almost nails him with a lovely slower one. Delivered between his thumb and fore finger, it looped  up before dipping in front of middle. Yuvraj manages to bring his bat down. Just in time.
length delivery outside off, driven past cover
retains the strike with a dab to thirdman

tip and run, Dravid is hit while making the crease. Pushed to right of point where Bravo swoops on it and fires a throw at the non-striker's end. Dravid is hit on the back of his right shoulder while making his crease
overpitched outside off, pushed down the ground
length delivery on the off, pushed to cover
kept a touch low and almost had Dravid. Full and on the middle, Dravid manages to keep it out
Top-edged four to thirdman region. Short and wide, Dravid threw his bat at it and it flies down fine
Another four. Dravid and India break free. A fine leg-glance. Poor bowling by Bravo though.
slower one turns into a low full-toss, Dravid picks it late and blocks it back down the track
on the legs, flicked past square-leg

What a shot! Classy straight drive. Overpitched allright but punched effortlessly down the ground. The high back-lift, the full face of the bat and the firm punch at the point of impact all made it real pleasure to watch
in the channel outside off, left alone
again well outside the off stump, Dravid lets this one to go through to the 'keeper as well.
on the stumps this time, Dravid gets a chance to put bat on ball but drives it straight into the stumps at the other end
Lovely on drive between the bowler and mid-on. Dravid continues to press on. Overpitched on the middle and leg, he leant forward to drive it down the ground
Bravo, after an expensive last over - 13 runs, is given another over. Starts off with a fullish delivery on the middle, pushed back down the track
on the legs, flicked past square-leg
In the zone outside the off stump, left alone
just short of driveable length outside the offstump, pushed to point
length delivery on the middle, pushed to mid-on. Tight over ends
angled across the left hander, left alone outside off stump
pitches on middle and leg and slants across Yuvraj who gets a stride in and pushes it to mid-off  for one
short of a length outside off, Dravid waits for it on the back foot and dabs it towards gully for a sharp single
punched to mid-off on the back foot
slower ball on off stump but Yuvraj spotted that and defended it on the back foot
banged in short, far too short, it bounces way over Yuvraj's head
driven crisply to cover
short of a length just outside off, Dravid times the square drive perfectly but Marlon Samuels dives superbly at point to restrict the batsmen to just one
angling into the left hander from round the wicket, played with an open face to point
imperious drive! Bravo gives Yuvraj the length and the width outside off stump, Yuvraj gets forward and beats the leather off the ball as it scorches past mid-off
a touch slower this time, Yuvraj plays the same drive but can't beat mid-off this time
whipped off the pads past square leg for one
good length and angling into yuvraj's middle stump from round the wicket, defended back to the bowler
a slower ball but it's far too full, Dravid picks it up early, waits for it and drives past the bowler, no stopping that as it races to the long-on fence
a touch shorter in length, whipped off the pads through square leg
defended to cover
played past point with an open face for one
dabbed past point for a single to bring up the 50-run partnership
short and wide outside off stump, Yuvraj flashes hard, a little too hard, at it and misses
pitches short of a length outside leg stump, Dravid gets across and easily works it down to fine leg for a single
shorth of a length outside off, Yuvraj unleashes another booming drive through cover but there's a sweeper in place and he prevents the boundary
slower ball and nearly in the blockhole, Yuvraj digs it out to point
a touch shorter, Yuvraj rocks back and drives through cover
a slower ball on middle and leg, Dravid got across his stumps a touch too early and manages an inside edge on to pad towards midwicket to move on to 49
short and wide outside off, Yuvraj tries to cut but gets beaten
fullish length but it's not as quick as Yuvraj would have liked, he drives it hard into the ground towards cover
full ball on the pads, Yuvraj tries to flick through midwicket but gets hit on the pads
he doesn't miss this time, the lofted flick flies over midwicket and to the fence
short of a length outside off, Yuvraj lets it go
dabbed to mid-on for a sharp single. Yuvraj retains strike
caught at cover! It was the slower ball, Yuvraj gets on the front foot and tries to play the lofted drive over cover, instead he ends up spooning it straight to Bravo
and another slower delivery beats the outside edge, Dhoni pushed tentatively at that outside the off stump, the left-armer's angle took the ball past his bat
defended to cover on the front foot, Bradshaw over-steps
short of a length, angling across Dhoni from over the wicket, left alone
full, straight on middle and slow as well, Dhoni defends on the off side
a touch shorter, inviting Dhoni to have a go outside off, he resists and lets it go

disaster for India! Dravid is run-out by a pick-and-throw from Dwayne Smith that any coach would be proud of. Dhoni dabs that towards midwicket and calls for the single, Smith runs across to square leg from midwicket, picks - he can see just one stump - and throws the stumps down that the non-strikers end, Dravid is short by a long way
driven to mid-off for one
defended on the off side
pushed back to the bowler on the front foot
shorter, flatter and quicker, Raina goes back and pushes it to mid-off for one
defended on the front foot
forced to long-on for a single
tight line, gives Dhoni no room or length to make use of, defended on the off side
sprayed wide outside off, called wide
whoops, he overcompensates by slipping it wide down leg side this time, same result
a touch short outside off, Dhoni dabs it down to short third man
he's back to his stock line and length, angling across the right hander after pitching on middle and off, Dhoni gets forward and defends to cover
slower ball on off stump, Dhoni opens the face of his bat and plays it to point
pitches outside off and moves away from the right hander, Dhoni lets it go
a touch fuller outside off, Dhoni leans onto the front foot and pushes it wide of Gayle at cover for a comfortable single
tossed up on off stump, Dhoni thumps it on the front foot but can't beat the fielder at cover
driven past the bowler down to long-off for one
defended on the front foot
shorter in length, Raina waits for it on the back foot and cuts to sweeper for one
fired in fast into the blockhole, Dhoni digs it out
dabbed to point for one, there's a direct hit at the bowler's end but Raina is home
a touch shorter in length on off and middle, driven to long-on off the back foot
a touch shorter again, angling into Raina from round the wicket, pushed down the ground on the back foot
forced off the back foot to sweeper
tight line, no room to work with, Raina dabs it short  of Lara at midwicket for a quick single
shorter in length and there's room outside off as well, Dhoni tries to beat short third man with the cut but doesn't
tossed up a fraction but that came down in Rania's blockhole, defended back to the bowler
dabbed short of point for a very sharp single
a touch shorter and Dhoni pushes down the ground for one
driven to long-off for a single
that kept a little low, Dhoni chops it down on the off side
on target right away, pitches just outside off and angles into Rania who pushes it to point on the back foot
defended to point again
a touch fuller in length on off and middle, Rania gets forward and pushes back to the bowler
that rises steeply on Rania from short of a length, he dabs it down on the off side, Dhoni sets off for the single but gets sent back because the fielder at point swoops down on it
banged in short again, Rania watches it carefully and defends back down the pitch
Taylor finishes off with a slower bacll, Raina can do little but defended back to the bowler, that's a maiden over
defended on the off side on the front foot
flat trajectory, angling into Dhoni's off stump, he gets forward and defends back to the bowler
dabbed towards Lara at midwicket for a sharp single, Lara is struggling to bend down and pick up the ball, remember he was declared fit minutes before the start of the game
struck on the pad but that pitched outside and hit the batsman outside leg stump
pushed down the ground for one
played to Lara at square leg again, this time he cuts off the single

short of a length angling into Rania who works it off the hips into a huge gap at square leg, Taylor sprints across and had his throw been accurate, Rania would have struggled to make his ground as he completed the second run
pushed to cover
full ball angling into the pads, pushed wide of the fielder at mid-on for a single
pitches short of a length on leg stump, Dhoni gets forward and gets hit on the glove
fullish in length and drifting on to the pads, Dhoni works it through square leg
short of a length, no room at all for the batsman, Rania defends on the back foot
pushed through quickly on off stump, played to cover
defended to midwicket
a touch shorter, Dhoni dabs it past point for one
driven to cover on the front foot
fuller in length, Rania drives straighter down the ground for one
defended back to the bowler, just three runs in that over
pitches short of a length on leg stump and drifts further down leg, wide called
good length, pitches just outside off and comes into Rania with the angle to cramp hi9m for room, defended to point
a touch fuller on off stump, Rania pushes it to Bravo at point
a touch shorter in length, Rania plays it to Lara at midwicket but can't steal the single this time
defended to cover on the back foot, this is stifiling bowling
a fraction short on off stump, Rania punches it past the bowler for a single
Taylor tries to finish a superb over with a slower ball but sprays it wide outside off
back on target after that blip, tight line on off stump, defended on the front foot
defended to Lara at point
worked off the pads to deep square leg for two
a touch fuller, Rania charges and drives it hard into the ground and straight to cover
a fraction short and Rania rocks back and cuts between point and short third man for one

fired in fast into the blockhole outside off stump, Rania tries to back away and make room but gets beaten, Baugh is quick to whip off the bails, it's a tight call for the third umpire to make, he has to decide is any part of the foot was behind the line, the third umpire rules that the foot was on the line and Rania is out
defended back to the bowler
turned off the pads behind square on the leg side
pushed on the front foot back to the bowler
forced down the ground on the back foot for one
whipped off the pads through midwicket for one
driven through cover on the back foot for one
angling into middle stump from over the wicket, defended back to the bowler
pushed to cover for a single, Gayle shies at the striker's end and concedes an overthrow
dabbed down to fine leg for one
defended to Bravo at midwicket
a touch short, Harbhajan waits for it and late cuts it to short third man
pushed to point for a single to end the over
low full toss, Dhoni drives to long-on for one
fullish length, Harbhajan plays a wispy drive down to long-off for one
a fraction short outside off, Dhoni plays the late cut and beats short third man, it's his first boundary off his 46th ball
pushed to midwicket for one
dabbed wide of short third man for one
Gayle drops short and Dhoni forces it through midwicket for a single and retains strike
floated slowly through the air on off stump, defended to cover
defended to square leg
full ball, Dhoni drives wide off mdiwkcte for one
full and straight, Harbhajan plays the slog sweep to deep midwicket for a single
dabbed to point for one
shorter in length, Harbhajan opens the face and plays it to short third man
full ball on middle stump, Harbhajan whips it over midwicket
driven to long-off for one
finally Dhoni cuts loose, gives Gayl the harge and hoists it high and over the midwicket fence, the crowd go into raptures
encore! Dhoni charges again, he's not to the pitch of the ball but goes through with the hoick over midwicket, he connects perfectly and it sails over the fence
late cut down to third man for a couple to end a productive over for India
fast and it's aimed at Harbhajan's blockhole, driven down the ground for one
superb ball, bang in the blockhole, Dhoni drives down the ground for one, Samuels doing the right thing by not allowing him to get under the ball
another one in the blockhole, pushed down the ground for another single
full toos worked through midwicket for one
a touch shorther and Harbhajan Singh gets into the act by biffing it straight down the ground for four
fired into the pads, Harbhajan is beaten for pace and gets a leg bye on the off side
he produces the yorker first up, dug out to square leg for one
and another yorker, this is exceptional death bowling, Dhoni plays his trademark whiplash shot down the ground for one
and goodbye Harbhajan! That's just outside off stump and Harbhajan throws everything behind that heave but drags it back on to his stumps
slower ball first up to Agarkar, beaten outside the off stump
another one in the block hole, Agarkar didn't know too much about that but managed a run on the off side
full ball on middle and off, Dhoni gets down and tries to paddle it on the leg side, the ball hits the pad and the batsmen run a leg bye

he tries to find the blockhole straight waya, Dhoni whips it to deep midwicket and calls for two, he dives spectacularly, full length, bat outstretched to make his ground at the strikers end, the crowd cheers as the third umpire rules him not out
Bravo produces another yorker, splendid bowling but Dhoni makes room and biffs it down the ground, Dhoni and Agarkar race through for two, they were too hasty because the umpire signals one-short
driven to long-off for two more, Dhoni is farming the strike and two short of fifty
another attempted yorker, Dhoni flicks through midwicket and races for two to bring up his fifty, he looks exhausted because he has been running like the wind
driven down the ground again and Dhoni again calls for two, this time the throw from the deep is an accurate one, Baugh breaks the stumps at the striker's end and Dhoni is millimetres short
he gets beaten off the last ball of the innings, Agarkar calls for the single anyway but Baugh throws the stumps down at the striker's end to dismiss Agarkar

inn2.comm: Two slips in place, he starts off with a wide down the leg side.
on the money this time, pushed back down the track

beauty this time. Almost had a lbw with a curving outswinger. It was full and on the off stump and curves away, Gayle is rapped on the pads but outside the off stump as he ends up pushing inside the line
Free gift to Chanders. Slipping down the leg side, and tickled fine
reaches out to a outswinger well outside the off stump and steers it to cover
lands on the off stump line, curves away, Chanders pushes it out to cover point
in the zone outside the off stump, moves away after pitching, left alone
leans forward to a length-delivery on the off stump line, bat and pad together, to push it to cover. It hit the front pad first before going on to hit the bat

Huge appeal for a  catch behind. Umpire Harper turns it down. It was pushed across and Gayle had a poke at it. Dhoni, the slip fielders and Munaf Patel went up in appeal. Replays suggest that there might have been a deflection but the snickometer doesn't show any evidence of any deflection! Much fun!
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
whack! Short and outside off, Gayle frees his mind and his arms. Through the extra cover gap. Stand and deliver stuff.
Pathan follows it up with a much fuller delivery, hint of outswing, Gayle gets behind it to push it to the off side
Swing and a miss. Full and outside the off stump, Gayle couldn't resist a drive.
landed on the back of a  length around the middle and leg, curved away, Gayle adjusted to push it to the off side
in the channel outside offstump, left alone
pushes it down the leg side.
lands on the middle, goes straight on with the angle, turned to square-leg
on the off and middle, full in length, Chanderpaul leans forward, head over the ball, pushes it to the off side
fuller, on the middle and off, driven back to Munaf who half-stops it
takes this one outside the offstump, left alone
straightens after landing on a length around middle and leg, tucked to square-leg
in the zone outside off, left alone.
seals the maiden with a cracker. It landed on the length around the off stump, drawing Chanderpaul forward before slanting away from him. Beaten neck and crop.
Nonchalant waft of the bat and the ball  races past the bowler. A low swinging full-toss, just outside the off stump, swatted down the ground

Raina drops Gayle! Gayle drills a fullish ball to right of short cover, Raina goes low to his right but couldn't hold on. Should have, could have, might have.. Go ask Sidhu .. .he will tell you a nice line about it.
take that! overpitched outside off, dwon came the flashing blade. blink. ball pings the cover fence
Whipped past square-leg. On the hips, up goes the right feet in the air, weight balanced on the left, and short-arm-jab sends the ball past square-leg
fullish on the off stump line, driven square to point
Again Munaf pings the channel, left alone
length delivery outside the off stump, Chanderpaul lets it go through to Dhoni
bit more effort at the time of release, the ball kicks up a bit from the length around that off stump, Chanderpaul adjusts to push it away towards cover point
Again Munaf beats Chanderpaul to end the over. In the zone, just outside the off stump and Chanders pokes at it tentatively
RP Singh at long-leg makes a mess of a regular stop and turns a single into a four. Full and on the legs, flicked away by Gayle.
on the middle, pushed back down the track
full and hint of inswing, Gayle chooses to play it on the off side, resists temptation to flick it away, out towards mid-off
pushed across Gayle who lets it go. West Indies' fans must be hoping that Gayle can continue to exhibit such kind of patience. Indian fans of course will hope for a brain explosion.
Monk-like patience. Leans forward, head over the ball, block.
on the leg and middle, veers away, Gayle tries to tickle it around the corner but misses and is hit on the pads
Again just outside the off stump, Chanderpaul pushes it to point.
Squares-up Chanderpaul with a length delivery on the off and that slants away from the left-hand batsman. Pushed to point.
this one holds its line after landing on a length around the middle and off, tickled around the corner to fine-leg. Now Gayle will face Munaf. Should be interesting!
And it does! Gayle backs away and just biffs it across the line through the midwicket. It was a length delivery on the stumps!
on the hips, worked past square-leg
on the legs, tucked to Irfan Pathan at long-leg
whipped past square-leg! back-of-length delivery on the middle and leg, Gayle pushes back and whips it away
leans forward to block. Ah!
just outside the off stump, slightly short of length, allows Gayle to punch it but he sends it straight to mid-on
speared in on the off stump, moving away slightly, Gayle adjusts to that movement, pushes it to cover point
much fuller by Agarkar and just outside the off stump, inviting a drive but no thankyou says Gayle who lets it go through to the 'keeper
on the leg and middle, why would you bowl there?, whipped with ease
Chanderpaul gets off the strike with a run-down to the thirdman
Did Gayle again back away, you ask? Nah. he stood there and punched a fullish ball powerfully but hit it straight to mid-off

oh ho! Gayle does back away this time and commits suicide. Tries to force a back of a length delivery on the off stump line over mid-off, rather out of ground, ends up spooning it up to RP Singh at mid-off. The ball took some time to come under the influence of gravity and when it did, it nestled into waiting palms
full and pushed to extra cover
on the off stump line, on a length, moves away slightly after pitching, pushed to point
slanted across, left alone.
slanting in, turned to square-leg
well outside the off stump, left alone
again outside the off stump, Bravo shuffles across to cover the stumps before shouldering arms
again well outside the off stump, inviting Bravo to have a go but he resists
Bravo pushes a length delivery to right of point, wants a single but Chanderpaul, wisely, turns it down
Chanderpaul breaks free with a flowing drive through covers.
again he caresses one on-the-up and nearly gets it through the same gap as the previous one. Not much pace behind this one though.

Length delivery just outside the offstump and it came back in a touch, Bravo nearly chokes himself by pushing his front leg too much across and has to end up going around it to put bat to ball. Manages it, else it would have been close.
outside the offstump, dabbed to thirdman
on the middle and off, defended off the front foot
whipped behind square-leg. It was full and outside the offstump, Chanderpaul leans forward and works his wrists over time.
on the off, pushed to cover point
pushed across, full in length, Chanderpaul moves towards the ball, stretches his right leg out, and pushes the ball to extra cover
length delivery on the offstump line, Chanderpaul opens the face of the bat to run it down to thirdman
Agarkar again tries to ping that well-outside-the-offstump line that he has been bowling to Bravo, ends up pushing it too wide
on the middle, pushed to Pathan at mid-on
in the zone outside the offstump, Bravo eases forward, pushes it to right of Raina at cover
just a dot ball but lovely cricket allround. Whiplash square-drive from Bravo, acrobatic dive from Yuvraj Singh at point
short, pulled powerfully but straight to square-leg. Lucky RP, unlucky Chanders

oh ho! almost popped a catch to Sehwag at square-leg. Again banged in short, this time with bit more effort, and it climbs shoulder high at Chanderpaul who went for his pull but the bottom-hand slipped out of the bat-handle and ball landed behind square-leg
Everything clicked perfectly this time for Chanderpaul. Again short and he swivelled it pull it behind square
Even better. A short-arm-jab sends another short delivery past the ropes, this time in front of square.
good length to resume, and Bravo lets it go by uninterrupted
on the spot again, but this time dabbed into the leg-side for a jogged single
that's a beautiful stroke! Over the wicket, overpitched and right into Chanderpaul's slot. The ball scuds over the damp outfield and all the way through the covers
oops - and now a wide, way down the leg-side. India are losing their way a bit at the moment
better channel, outside off stump, but too wide to be tempted into a stroke
lovely delivery! That's more like it from Singh, outside off stump, perfect seam, swung away from a loose drive, but no nick
and another good delivery to finish, pushed up into the blockhole but Chanderpaul snicks a drive safely down to third man
a little bit airborne this time, as Chanderpaul shovels the ball out to midwicket. But safe&
ripper! Huge rotations on the ball, perfect length and zipped over off stump. An absorbing battle in prospect
pushed into the leg side to escape the strike
squeals from behind the stumps as Harbhajan gets it on the money again. Lovely bowling
fully forward this time, and smothers the spin
shoulders arms to a off-stump turner. Nice over
outside off, left well alone
drawn forward, pushed out to point
very tidy flick off the hips, good roll of the wrists to pick the gap at midwicket and another couple to the total
width and driven off the back foot and square, but swept up on the cover boundary
oops, that's a bit shoddy at midwicket. The fielder dives straight over the ball, and another pair onto the total
on the off stump line, punched back to Harbhajan
tossed up outside the off stump, Chanderpaul eases forward to push it to cover
just outside the off stump, tapped on the head, ball rolls towards point
turns from outside off, left alone. Chanderpaul earns his living playing this kind of a waiting game.
on the stumps, turned to midwicket. He is not going to take any risks.
he doesn't. Another dot ball as he refuses to indulge despite Harbhajan flighting one up outside the off stump
swing and a miss.  Young Bravo is not so patient. Chases a wide delivery, doesn't connect.
slanted delivery, jumps up a bit from the length, Bravo pushes at it, away from his body, to steer it down to Agarkar at thirdman
full and comes in with the angle around the off stump line, driven to mid-off
spears in on the leg and middle, slides down with the angle, Chanderpaul is rapped on the pads as he falls over a touch while trying to work it to the on side
Super shot. Caressed through the covers. No violence, just a gentle push-drive. Overpitched outside off and the blade came down in a nice little arc.&
on the off stump, turning in, defended off the front foot
doosra on the off stump line, it straightened rather than turn away, Bravo ends up pushing inside the line and gets an outside edge which takes the ball to short thirdman
nice teasing delivery outside the off stump. well-flighted one and it turned after pitching and had Chanderpaul groping a bit. Runs off the outside edge to short thirdman
on the off stump line, turning in slightly, pushed back to the bowler

Harbhajan gets his man. Beaten in flight and then by the turn. Bravo was hanging back at his crease, preferring to play the spin off the pitch. Harbhajan flights this one on the off and middle stump line,  turns it past the defensive-blade and thuds into the pads. Would have hit the leg stump.
Starts off with a loosener - well short of length, Chanderpaul pulls it nonchalantly through the midwicket gap
41st ODI fifty up for Chanderpaul. Very well played Sir. He leant forward to a fullish delivery to ease it past point to bring up the landmark
in the zone outside the offstump, left alone
short of length and on the hips, bad line and length, whipped to right of square-leg where Sehwag dives to make the stop
And again. Another woeful short delivery and Chanderpaul pulls it hard but Sehwag, at square-leg, cuts it off
turns in from outside the offstump, Sarwan goes back and across to push it close on the offside
Flatter and quicker, whipped to midwicket where Yuvraj Singh dives to his right to make the stop
on the leg and middle, Sarwan helps it to fine-leg with the spin, Sehwag comes across to make the stop

oh! it goes through the legs of Suresh Raina at short-leg. It was tossed up on the middle, Sarwan pushes at it with the spin. It was a difficult chance all right but Raina was in no position to take it anyways. He had almost turned to his right, shying away from the drive and the ball went between his legs
beaten by the flight. Outside the offstump and Chanderpaul goes for a drive, and is beaten as the ball dips rapidly and turns away
length delivery on the off stump line, Sarwan pushes it to cover
delivered from close to the stumps and on the middle and leg stump line, tucked away to square-leg
slapped past extra cover. Mind you it was a length delivery but Sarwan hit it on the up and past cover.
Defends this one with the full face of the bat
nice little straight drive but Munaf Patel gets a hand to it.
Sarwan retains the strike with a dab to thirdman
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan gets forward and tucks it off his pads to midwicket
pushed  through flatter, Sarwan plays back and defends back to Harbhajan
full ball, the doosra, defended on the off side
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan takes a step down and drives to mid-on
drifting on to middle and leg this time, Sarwan gets across and tucks it behind square for one
pushed quicker through the air into Chanderpaul from round the wicket, defended back to the bowler
drifts on to middle and leg, flicked off the pads but doesn't beat square leg
slips down leg side
angled into middle and leg again, defended behind square leg
poor line from Sehwag, angling into Sarwan's pads, he gets across and gets a glove down to fine leg
another wide down leg side, the dew factor seems to be taking effect
full outside off stump, Sarwan drives through cover for one

caught at slip, the well-set Chanderpaul goes. Sehwag comes round the wicket to Chanderpaul, angles the ball into the left-hander, pitches around off stump and turns it away, Chanderpaul pokes tentatively at it and nudges it into Dravid's hands
full on middle and leg, flicked to midwicket
a touch quicker from Harbhajan and it is the straighter one, Sarwan plays back and defends
a little shorter in length and too straight, Sarwan works it off his pads for a couple
defended back to the bowler
again it's short of a length on middle stump, Sarwan gets across and flicks behind square
pitches outside off, turns in and hits Morton on the pad, the batsman had got a stride in and was probably hit outside the line of off stump
drifting on to middle and leg, Sarwan gets on to the back foot in a flash and nudges it down to fine leg
pitches outside off, spins into Morton who tries to cut but misses, was there a bottom edge?
Morton plays the sweep and top edges it to deep square leg, luckily for him it falls safe
worked off the pads to square leg
Sarwan flicks off his pads to keep the strike, Sehwag is consistently drifting on to his middle and leg stump
pitches outside off, on a good length, Sarwan lunges forward and pads it away
pushed flatter and quicker outside off, played to point
fullish on off and middle, Sarwan gets across and flicks past Rania at short leg
shorter in length on off stump, Morton goes on the back foot and dabs to short third man
Harbhajan pushes it quickly through on Sarwan's off stump, defended on the back foot
dropped short outside off stump, Morton goes on the back foot and forces it to cover
angled into middle and leg yet again, Sarwan waits for it and the ball clips the pad and rolls down towards fine leg
bowled wide down leg, he will have to re-bowl that
defended on the front foot
that's poor bowling, another wide down leg side
defended to cover on the front foot
tossed up on off stump, Morton gets a stride in, the ball hits the pad and lobs to short leg, the Indians let out a muted appeal
angled into the pads, worked down to fine leg
full ball on off stump, driven down the ground for one
flighted ball outside off stump, Sarwan plays forward tentatively and defends
tossed up on middle and off stump, Sarwan drives back to Yuvraj
floated through on off stump, Sarwan hits the cover drive extremely hard but straight to Kaif
dropped a touch shorter and much flatter, Sarwan goes on the back foot and cuts
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan gets on the front foot and defends on the off side
played to point, Sarwan wants one but Morton sends him back
played off the pads to short fine leg
defended to Rania at short leg
pushed through quicker on off stump, defended to point
good length ball, draws Morton forward and hits him on the front pad
dropped a touch short on middle and leg, worked off the pads to midwicket
tossed up on middle, Sarwan backs away and makes room to squeeze it down to third man
floated through outside off stump, Morton gives it a thump back to Yuvraj who dives to his left and stops runs
defended back to the bowler
eked to point for a risky single, Sarwan could have been it trouble had there been a direct hit
glanced down to fine leg
flighted ball on off stump, Sarwan gets forward and drops it between cover and point for one
shorter in length, defended to cover on the back foot
driven to long-off for a single
short of a length, Sarwan cuts to deep backward point, the second run is risky and Sarwan dives full length to make his ground, the third umpire rules him in, much to the disappointment of the crowd
defended to midwicket
nudged off the pads to square leg for another single, Sarwan is picking them off with minimum fuss
good length and flatter on off stump, defended back to Yuvraj
tossed up on middle, Sarwan tries to make room but drives back to Yuvraj
cut hard towards point where Tendulkar misfields to allow the single
Morton breaks the shackles by smashing one over the long-on fence, that six takes the pressure off him
pushed to cover on the back foot
cut to Tendulkar at point
worked off the pads to midwicket, Kaif fumbles it at first but the batsmen don't take the single
this time it's defended straight to Kaif at midwicket
and now it's flicked wide off Kaif for two to deep midwicket
dropped short, Sarwan plays back, waits for it and turns it behind square for one
defended to point
played on the front foot to square leg
driven to mid-on
he brings a second slip into place and drifts down leg side, worked down to fine leg for one
tossed up outside off, Sarwan leans across and flicks to midwicket
he works it into the gap between mid-on and midwicket this time for a single
a touch short and it bounced a little more, Morton plays back and guides it past Tendulkar at second slip for one to retain strike
tossed up on off stump, defended on the front foot
defended to midwicket
driven firmly to cover where Harbhajan misfields to allow the single
pushed to midwicket on the front foot
defended to midwicket yet again
quick ball outside off stump, dabbed to short fine leg but they decide against going for the single
pushed through quicker on off and middle, defended to short leg
dropped a touch short and Morton drives off the back foot through cover
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan gets on the front foot and drives to mid-off for one
straying on to middle and leg stump, worked down to fine leg
flatter ball on off stump, Sarwan opens the face and runs it down to third man
Morton pats it back to Harbhajan
a touch short outside off and Morton plays it towards point on the back foot, the crowd are cheering every dot ball
turned off the pads to fine leg for one
defended on the off side, more cheers from the crowd
patted down the ground for a single to bring up the 50-run partnership, off 83 balls
flicked through midwicket for one
short of a length outside off stump, driven on the back foot to cover, we're up to a run-a-ball now
strays on to the pads, flicked comfortably down to long leg for one
banged in short and Sarwan attempts the pull shot, he gets a bottom edge that runs fine past Dhoni for four
driven uppishly through extra cover, that was just out of Kaif's reach
well the ball is dry but it isn't helping Agarkar's control, sprayed wide down leg side
short outside off stump, Morton goes on the back foot and square drives to deep point
good length, tight line to finish a poor over, defended on the off side
driven hard into the ground and Sehwag collects it on the bounce
defended to midwicket
worked through the gap between midwicket and mid-on
pushed on the front foot, wide of Kaif at midwicket for another single
driven down the ground for one
pushed towards mid-on, Kaif runs across from midwicket to stop the single
Agarkar sprays it down leg side again, wide called
good length ball on middle stump, Morton tries to force it down the ground but ends up playing it to midwicket
short of a length outside of, Morton dabs it to cover, Sarwan dashes off from the non-striker's end, Morton sends him back
banged it short, it skids on to Morton who tries to pull but doesn't make proper contact
played to Yuvraj at point
short ball on middle and leg, Morton whips it off his hips to deep square leg for two
tight line, no room for the batsman, driven to cover on the back foot, Agarkar finishes a tight over, just three runs off it
Sehwag drifts on to Sarwan's pads, flicked to deep square leg
drifting on to middle and leg again, poor line from Sehwag, Morton flicks through midwicket for two, Yuvraj hould have stopped that in the infield
defended back to the bowler, the pressure on Morton is inching up
driven down the ground to long-on
full toss, driven to Tendulkar at mid-off, he slips on the wet outfield and concedes two
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan drives through cover for two to bring up his fifty, an excellent patient innings from Sarwan, well played!
yes, Morton does indeed get on with it, Agarkar bangs it in too short, Morton pulls it to the deep backward square leg fence
he replies with the yorker, and it swings into Morton's blockhole, dug out on the off side for one
short again, outside off stump, punched through cover on the back foot
short and wide outside off stump, hit hard but straight to cover
short of a length on middle stump, Morton punches to long on for a single, West Indies bring up 200
attempted yorker, dug out back to the bowler
defended back to the bowler, Pathan starts well with one that pitched short of a length and gave the batsman no room
driven hard into the ground, Pathan jumps up to field but only manages to slow it down as the batsmen run one to long-on
drifting on to the hips, tucked down to fine leg for one
short and wide outside off stump, Morton frees his arms and gives it a fierce whack, Kaif does extremely well to stop it cleanly at cover
poor ball, short and no pace on it at all, it sat up and said 'hit me' and Morton obliged by smacking it to the midwicket fence, he hit that so hard that he cracked his bat
dabbed to midwicket for a sharp single
flicked down to long leg
attempted yorker but it isn't quite in the blockhole, driven to long-on
driven hard but back to the bowler
attempted short ball but mis-directed down leg side
short ball, Sarwan gives him the charge and makes room to smack it through cover for one
and Morton is out lbw, he tried to pull a ball that pitched short but kept far too low, he missed and was hit plumb in front of middle stump
Agarkar sprays it so wide outside off that had Dhoni let it go, Dravid at first slip would have collected it
played to midwicket for a single, Lara is off and West Indies need ten more
driven back to Pathan
short of a length and that was quick, the ball squeezed through Lara's bat and pad, clips the thigh pad and goes through to Dhoni
gorgeous cover drive, that was short and wide outside off stump, Lara flays it through the off side as if to say  that's how it's done
he's chopped it on! Lara backed away to make room and had a wild swing at it, he gets a bottom edge on to leg stump
dabbed to Yuvraj at point

slower ball, Samuels skies the pull shot, Dravid drops the catch at midwicket but he throws the ball to the nonstriker's end and Sarwan who was trying to complete the second run is well short, it's all going a bit crazy out there
bowled him, Smith tries to heave it down the ground and misses completely, the ball crashes into the stumps, unbelieveable stuff
slips down leg side, umpire Harper says that's not wide, close call but it was close to leg stump
dabbed short on the off side for one, Agarkar shies at the bowler's end but misses or that would have been out
Samuels wins it for West Indies! Short and wide outside off stump, not a very good ball and Samuels slashes hard  at it, the ball flies wide of third man for four to finish the match
